arm_group.description: Each osteopathic session is based on structural evaluation and treatment using indirect techniques.

Sham therapy was administered with subjects lying supine on the treatment table while the operator used light manual contact to "treat" the subject. A pre-determined protocol has been used. The practitioner's attention was distracted by subtracting calculation in silence.

brief_summary.textblock:
The aim of the present study is to determine the extend to which osteopathic manipulative
      treatment (OMT) is effective on a sample of healthy subjects in changing high frequency (HF)
      parameters.

clinical_study.brief_title: Osteopathic Manipulative Treatment Effects on High Frequency Parameters in Healthy Subjects

primary_outcome.measure: Change from baseline high frequency (HF) value at 1 week
